</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1436,1697,1974]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis box="[199,414,1769,1794]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Additional remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Philippi" box="[428,654,1769,1794]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" refString="Philippi, R. A. (1852 b) Centuria quinta testaceorum novorum. (Contin.) Zeitschrift fur Malakozoologie, 9 (2), 20 - 29. [25 March; p. 32]" type="journal article" year="1852" yearSuffix="a">
Philippi (
<number box="[531,591,1769,1794]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" value="1852.0">1852</number>
a: 
<number box="[614,645,1769,1794]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" value="53.0">53</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, by stating “Betrachten wir indessen die von Lamarck citirte Figur der Encyclopädie als 
<typeStatus box="[348,416,1806,1830]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Typus</typeStatus>
seiner Art” [considering the figure of Lamarck in the 
<emphasis box="[1019,1310,1805,1830]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Encyclopédie Méthodique</emphasis>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1806,1830]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">type</typeStatus>
of his species], designated that specimen as the 
<typeStatus box="[689,792,1841,1866]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<emphasis box="[808,867,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Code</emphasis>
, Art. 74.5). Although 
<taxonomicName box="[1119,1208,1842,1866]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ampullariidae" genus="Ampullaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Melanosporales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[1119,1208,1842,1866]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of Schumacher was listed as a new name by Sherborn (
<number box="[556,617,1877,1902]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" value="1926.0">1926</number>
: 
<number box="[629,689,1878,1902]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" value="2309.0">2309</number>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Schumacher" box="[710,991,1877,1902]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" refString="Schumacher, C. F. (1817) Essai d'un nouveau systeme des habitations des vers testaces. Schultz, Copenhagen, [ii] + 287 pp., 22 pls. [after 1 March; p. 20] http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 35863" type="book" year="1817">
Schumacher (
<number box="[866,927,1878,1902]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" value="1817.0">1817</number>
: 
<number box="[940,983,1878,1902]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" value="200.0">200</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
in fact treated 
<taxonomicName box="[1166,1255,1878,1902]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ampullariidae" genus="Ampullaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Melanosporales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[1166,1255,1878,1902]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(presumably of Lamarck) as the valid name of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus" authorityName="Linnaeus" box="[545,796,1913,1938]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ampullariidae" genus="Ampullaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Melanosporales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ampullacea">
<emphasis box="[545,676,1913,1938]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">ampullacea</emphasis>
Linnaeus
</taxonomicName>
, probably because he was a strong supporter of the Lamarckian rather than the Linnaean system (see the introduction to Schumacher’s work).
</paragraph>
